  <fr:li>for each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A,B:\mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex>, a function <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {hom}_{F} : \mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {C}}{\mathopen {}\left (A,B\right )\mathclose {}}\to \mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {D}}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathbf {ob}_{F}A,\mathbf {ob}_{F}B\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol><fr:p>In other words, a wild 0-functor is a homomorphism of the underlying graphs.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
