type="local"
href="jms-0037.xml"
addr="jms-0037"
title="Wild category">wild category</fr:link>, and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I:\mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex> be an object of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> such  that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Delta  I}\xrightarrow {{\alpha }}{1_{\mathcal {C}}}]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-0039.xml"
addr="jms-0039"
title="Wild natural transformation">wild natural transformation</fr:link> from the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-003D.xml"
addr="jms-003D"
title="The wild constant functor">constant 0-functor</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathcal {C}}\xrightarrow {{\Delta  I}}{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex> to the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-003C.xml"
addr="jms-003C"
title="The wild identity functor">identity 0-functor</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathcal {C}}\xrightarrow {{1_{\mathcal {C}}}}{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> for some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I:\mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex>. Now let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r:\mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {C}}{\mathopen {}\left (I,J\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s:\mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {C}}{\mathopen {}\left (J,I\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> be a section-retraction pair witnessed by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta  : s;r = 1_{I}]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma  : r;s=\alpha _{I}]]></fr:tex> be a splitting of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _{I}:\mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {C}}{\mathopen {}\left (I,I\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. Then we may define a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-0039.xml"
addr="jms-0039"
title="Wild natural transformation">wild natural transformation</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Delta  J}\xrightarrow {{\beta }}{1_{\mathcal {C}}}]]></fr:tex> and an identification <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi  : \beta _{J} = 1_{J}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>(This construction is due to <fr:link
type="external"
href="https://homotopytypetheory.org/2018/11/26/impredicative-encodings-part-3/">Mike Shulman</fr:link>.)</fr:p>
 
   
